{
  "texts": [
    "Our study contributes to and expands prior research in two main literature streams.",
    "First, we contribute to the literature stream of artificial intelligence (AI) for examplebased learning in heuristic domains.",
    "Most prior research (van Gog et al., 2008; van Gog & Rummel, 2010; Renkl et al., 2009; Renkl, 2002) on example-based learning uses static examples: both the examples and explanations are created by experts and all the learners see the exact same content, independent of their input.",
    "In contrast to past literature, RELEX provides examples tailored to the needs of the learner in terms of topic (i.e.",
    "similar content) and skill level."
  ]
}